dentification. By chronicling this evolution in thinking, Hammerschlag ultimately reveals how the figural Jew can function as a critical mechanism that exposes the political dangers of mythic allegiance, whether couched in universalizing or particularizing terms. Both an intellectual history and a philosophical argument, The Figural Jew will set the agenda for all further consideration of Jewish identity, modern Jewish thought, and continental philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewish philosophyzFrancey20th century. 0aJewsxIdentity. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy20th century. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  apolitical, politician, wartime, france, thinker, intellectual, philosophy, philosophical, philosopher, academic, scholarly, research, jewish, judaism, religion, religious, faith, belief, homeland, history, historical, nature, 20th, century, nationalist, nationalism, rhetoric, modern, culture, cultural, bias, wwii, prewar, literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022631511940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226315133423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226315133/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles